min:
"Columbia Heights is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood in Washington, DC. Steeped in history, the area boasts a rich past, including a significant role in the civil rights movement. Today, it is a bustling community with a lively arts scene, trendy restaurants, and unique shopping experiences. The neighborhood is conveniently located near public transportation, with the Columbia Heights Metro Station (Green and Yellow lines) just a few blocks away and multiple bus lines servicing the area. A wide variety of restaurants and bars can be found along 11th Street and 14th Street, catering to all tastes and budgets. Just a short walk away is the beautiful Malcolm X Park (also known as Meridian Hill Park), a popular spot for picnics, outdoor activities, and the famous Sunday Drum Circle.

By staying in Columbia Heights, guests will have easy access to all the amenities and experiences that make this neighborhood an exciting and welcoming place to explore."

‚≠êNEIGHBORHOOD ‚≠ê
Anacostia is an up-and-coming neighborhood, likely the last unpolished gem in DC. It has been undergoing significant changes in the past few years. However, it is not a picture-perfect, manicured neighborhood like Georgetown. Depending on where you're coming from, you may see different aspects of the community. Some parts are still rough-looking, while others showcase a new, updated, and hip side. We love living here, but it might not be everyone's cup of tea. Please note that there are no stores or amenities within walking distance. The Navy Yard, with its shops, bars, and restaurants, is about 2.5 miles or a 6-minute drive away.
